UID:260405GyMaEchi3EW14bx1jU59vw
DESCRIPTION:Sonoma County is incredibly rich in biodiversity: although it 
 covers only about 1% of California’s land area\, it is estimated to cont
 ain around 20% of the state’s biodiversity in a particularly diverse por
 tion of the Sonoma Valley.\n\nThis program\, presented in Spanish by Jack 
 London State Historic Park and the Sonoma Ecology Center\, will teach you 
 to use your phone to easily and enjoyably identify birds\, plants\, and an
 imals.\n\nThis program is designed as the first part of a three-part serie
 s focused on observing and identifying nature in Sonoma County:\n\nPart I.
  (July 4\, 2026) Join us at the Sonoma Valley Library for an interactive t
 alk where you’ll learn how to use the Merlin Bird ID and iNaturalist app
 s\, two of the most popular and useful tools for identifying wildlife.\n\n
 Part II. (April 24\, 2026) Use what you learned in the library to identify
  birds in Jack London State Historic Park with the help of Merlin Bird ID.
 \n\nPart III. (April 25\, 2026) Use what you learned in the library to ide
 ntify plants and animals in Sugarloaf Ridge State Park with the help of iN
 aturalist.\n\nThis workshop will focus on:\n\nHow to use Merlin Bird ID to
  identify birds by song and photo\n\n• How to use iNaturalist to identif
 y and document plants\, birds\, insects\, and other animals\n\n• Basic t
 ips for observing nature and improving your identification skills\n\n• G
 eneral information about common birds\, plants\, and animals in Sonoma Val
 ley and Sonoma County\n\n• How these apps help scientists and parks prot
 ect local biodiversity\n\nThis program\, presented in Spanish\, is ideal f
 or beginners\, families\, nature lovers\, and anyone curious. No prior exp
 erience is necessary. We will go step by step\, and there will be time for
  questions and guided practice.\n\nThis workshop will serve as preparation
  for guided walks on April 24 and 25 at Jack London State Historic Park an
 d Sugarloaf Ridge State Park\, where we will put what we've learned into p
 ractice in the field.\n\nFor more information\, contact Carlos Barragán a
 t cbarragan@jacklondonpark.com or call 707-938-5216 ext. 9.
LOCATION:Sonoma Valley Library
URL:https://jacklondonpark.com/events/especiesdesonoma/
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
