UID:260401SyrwqCIwX0OTueDRqtlE7g
DESCRIPTION:**The Art of Visible Mending: Honeycomb Darning**\n\nHoneycomb
  darning is a structured\, decorative technique that reinforces knitwear w
 hile adding texture and pattern. In this hands-on workshop\, you’ll lear
 n how to mend worn or thinning areas using a durable lattice-style stitch 
 designed especially for knits.\n\n**In this workshop you’ll:**\n\n• Le
 arn the fundamentals of honeycomb darning\n\n• Choose appropriate yarn a
 nd materials for knit repair\n\n• Create a structured mend on a practice
  swatch\n\n• Explore design choices to make your repair subtle or bold\n
 \nBring a knit garment to mend or practice with provided materials. All su
 pplies included.
LOCATION:Gather Sebastopol
