DESCRIPTION:Schedule\n\nTuesday\, April 7\, 2026 5:30 PM – 8:00 PM\n\nEx
 perience Level\n\nAll Levels\n\nEvent Categories: Bilingual\, Culinary Art
 s\n\nAge\\(s\\)\n\n18 and older\n\n$100 – Registration Cost\n\nMaster th
 e art of empanada making with both sweet and savory fillings. Learn dough 
 techniques\, folding methods\, and create delicious handheld pastries.\n\n
 What you’ll do\n\nDiscover the versatility of empanadas in this hands-on
  culinary class where you’ll master both sweet and savory variations of 
 this beloved pastry. Learn to create tender\, flaky dough from scratch and
  explore traditional filling techniques that balance flavor and texture. Y
 ou’ll prepare savory empanadas with options like seasoned beef\, chicken
 \, cheese and vegetables\, alongside sweet versions featuring fruit\, choc
 olate\, or dulce de leche. Instruction covers proper dough handling\, fold
 ing and crimping techniques for beautiful presentation\, and cooking metho
 ds including baking and frying. You’ll understand how to adjust moisture
  levels in fillings to prevent soggy pastries and learn tips for making em
 panadas ahead for easy entertaining. Whether you’re drawn to traditional
  Latin American recipes or creative fusion flavors\, this class gives you 
 the skills to make professional-quality empanadas at home. P
LOCATION:Sonoma Community Center
