 ation\n\nRoom 110\n\nExperience Level\n\nAll Levels\n\nFamily\, Kids\n\nAg
 e\\(s\\)\n\n7-12\n\nAll children must be accompanied by an adult to attend
 .\n\n$30 – Per Family\, max of 3 people. Learn ancient stick loom weavin
 g in this hands-on class. Create a beautiful tapestry using natural materi
 als\, simple techniques\, and your choice of colors.\n\nAbout the Class\n\
 nCome learn the ancient craft of weaving with a stick loom! In this family
 -friendly class\, you’ll learn to hand-weave a simple tapestry using sti
 cks as your loom. The demonstration will include setting up the warp threa
 ds\, learning a simple over-under stitch pattern and the final knot step. 
 There will be a variety of stick shapes to choose from and plenty of room 
 to play with pattern and color. And voila! You’ll leave the class with y
 our stick-loom tapestry \\(either in progress or completed\, depending on 
 the chosen scale\\). Hang your weaving on your wall to bring nature indoor
 s or from a tree to bring your artistry outside! This class is open to par
 ents with their children ages 7 through 12.
LOCATION:Sonoma Community Center
URL:https://sonomacommunitycenter.org/programs/family-stick-loom-weaving/
