BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Making Citrus Curd with Merrilee Olson at Gold Ridge Organic Farms
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260410T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260410T130000
UID:260401Psbi4udaHke9XltT6NsSbQ
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a hands-on citrus curd making class led by chef an
 d food preservationist Merrilee Olson. Over three hours\, Merrilee will gu
 ide you through every step of making silky\, vibrant citrus curd — shari
 ng her expert techniques and secrets for achieving that perfect balance of
  tart\, sweet\, and luscious — using organic Meyer Lemons and Satsuma Ma
 ndarins grown right here on our 88-acre farm.\n\nThe experience begins wit
 h a ride aboard our apple-themed trolley out to the Apple Cottage\, where 
 the class takes place surrounded by the beauty of the farm. Each guest wil
 l take home an apple-blossom pink apron\, a jar of the curd they made\, an
 d a bag of fresh organic lemons to put your new skills to the test!\n\nMer
 rilee Olson is a chef and food preservationist with years of experience tr
 ansforming farm-fresh ingredients into culinary treasures. As the founder 
 of Preserve Farm Kitchens\, she has dedicated her work to celebrating seas
 onal produce and the timeless art of preservation\, bringing creativity\, 
 expertise\, and a deep love of good food to every class she teaches.
LOCATION:Gold Ridge Organic Farms
URL:https://www.exploretock.com/gold-ridge-organic-farms/event/600035/citr
 us-curd-workshop-with-merrilee-olson
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Juke Joint Jukebox
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260410T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260410T213000
UID:260401IDZsVU_zekqaJSTl-NcmIg
DESCRIPTION:Returning to Spreckels\, Juke Joint Jukebox is an electrifyin
 g educational cabaret that brings the legends to life — Ella Fitzgerald\
 , Ray Charles\, Dorothy Dandridge\, Harry Belafonte\, and more. Part conce
 rt\, part history lesson\, this high-octane journey celebrates the artists
  who shaped American music with powerhouse vocals\, storytelling\, and irr
 esistible rhythm.\n\nJuke Joint Jukebox features the vocal talents of Gar
 y Stanford Jr.\, Bradley Kynard\, Skylaer Palacios\, Sharon Griffith\, Sol
 ona Husband\, Julie Dormire and Leo Kimuyu. They are joined by pianist Vic
 tor Hall\, guitarist Greg Call\, and drummer Lance Lee.\n\nFilled with soa
 ring songs\, poignant storytelling and live music\, Juke Joint Jukebox is
  a special event not to be missed!
LOCATION:Spreckels Center for the Performing Arts
URL:https://app.arts-people.com/index.php?show=316486
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Kearsley Home Furnishings Moving Sale
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260410T110000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260410T173000
UID:2604015Kv4Vn6gwkaxb-YvWxCP5Q
DESCRIPTION:Kearsley\, Sonoma’s renowned luxury linen and textile atelie
 r\, is relocating. In preparation\, the atelier has released its Kearsley 
 and Barbara Beckmann inventory at rare\, decisive pricing\, beginning at 5
 0% off.\n\nThe sale includes in-stock bed linens\, duvet covers\, coverlet
 s\, sheets\, pillowcases\, shams\, and outdoor pillows\, as well as fine f
 abrics by the yard for upholstery and drapery. Also available are hotel sa
 mple robes\, antique furniture\, a sleigh bed\, original artwork\, and rar
 e textile pieces seldom offered to the public.\n\nA broader selection is a
 vailable in-store\, including one-of-a-kind furnishings and collector-leve
 l pieces not listed online.\n\nKearsley is located through the Orchard Pla
 ce driveway entrance at Winery Sixteen 600\, and can also be accessed dire
 ctly from First Street West. The atelier is situated upstairs\, in the bac
 k of the beautiful yellow building.\n\nThis is a limited opportunity to ac
 quire exceptional design work from one of Sonoma’s most distinctive atel
 iers. Ideal for interior designers\, private clients\, collectors\, and th
 ose seeking truly special gifts.\n\nIn-store at 561 First Street West\, So
 noma\, and online at kearsleyhome.com April 1 through April 17\, while sel
 ections last.
LOCATION:Kearsley Sonoma Atelier
URL:https://kearsleyhome.com/collections/moving-sale
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
