BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Healdsburg International Short Film Festival Audience Favorites
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260411T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260411T210000
UID:260401zhYZAJBYXUeaOKToWTcCHg
DESCRIPTION:The Healdsburg International Short Film Festival showcases w
 ork from filmmakers of all ages and from all walks of life\, with represen
 tative work from as many as 50 countries. Available genres vary each year\
 , but always include narrative fiction\, documentaries\, and animation. Th
 e films in HISFF’s “Audience Favorites” represent the very best of
  the festival’s screenings from last September\, across all genres. Vol
 ume 1 will screen at 2 pm and 7:30 pm on Saturday\, April 11th and at 5 p
 m on Sunday\, April 12th. Volume 2 will screen at 5 pm on Saturday\, Apr
 il 11th and at 2 pm and 7:30 pm on Sunday\, April 12th. See both volumes t
 o (re)experience the HISFF 2025 audience’s favorite comedies\, dramas\, 
 documentaries\, and animation. Laugh\, cry\, and experience the beauty of 
 storytelling with short films.\n\nWatch the official HISFF Audience Favori
 tes trailer!\n\nAbout HISFF: Our panel of notable judges from the entertai
 nment industry makes the HISFF an attraction for new and veteran filmmaker
 s alike — people like Ed Begley\, Jr.\, Laraine Newman\, Tom Waits\, an
 d so many more. Several judges attended in 2025\, including actor Ed Begle
 y\, Jr.\, who made a book-signing appearance at the Raven as part of festi
 val events. More festival judges are expected to attend in 2026\; read ab
 out the judges on the Raven’s festival webpage.\n\n**April 11-12**\, **
 2026**\n\n**VOL 1: Saturday:** 2:00 pm\; 7:30 pm. **Sunday:** 5:00 pm. *
 *VOL 2: Saturday:** 5:00 pm\; **Sunday:** 2:00 pm\; 7:30 pm. \n\n**Adul
 ts**: $20 per screening block (multiple films per block)\n\n**Students:**
  $10 per screening block (multiple films per block)
LOCATION:The Raven Performing Arts Theater
URL:https://raventheater.org/events/hisff-audience-favorites/
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:David Correa at Adobe Road Winery
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260411T163000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260411T190000
UID:260401xKpFBeqAjEqYkg39QwcHfw
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a special Saturday acoustic live music set at Adob
 e Road Winery in **Downtown Petaluma**. Sip on award-winning wines while 
 enjoying talented local musicians in a warm and inviting atmosphere. Choos
 e from wines by the glass or bottle to discover new favorites. Reserve you
 r spot on **Tock** and make it a memorable night of great music\, fine w
 ine\, and good company!\n\nDavid Correa is a celebrated guitarist and comp
 oser blending Latin rhythms with Spanish and world music influences. Since
  1999\, The David Correa Group has built a loyal fanbase across the Bay Ar
 ea and beyond with energetic\, rhythm-driven performances. The group has t
 oured extensively throughout the western U.S. and earned multiple accolade
 s\, including three consecutive NORBAY Awards for Best Latin Band. Correa 
 has released seven albums\, including *New Moon* and *Alta Vista*\, and
  has been featured alongside New Flamenco greats like Ottmar Liebert and J
 esse Cook. His live shows promise a vibrant mix of soulful guitar\, rhythm
 \, and musical storytelling.
LOCATION:Adobe Road Winery
URL:https://adoberoadwines.com/events/live-music-david-correa-april-11-202
 6/
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Renegade Orchestra at the Hall of the Above
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260411T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260411T204500
UID:260401uHUxLVnUlU2PB359Fsl8Eg
DESCRIPTION:The Renegade Orchestra is the bay area’s most rock and roll 
 symphony. Is it a rock band? Is it an orchestra? Who knows? But it’s def
 initely the best of both worlds. The pure unbridled fury of some of the ba
 y area’s top orchestra players unleashed on classic rock songs backed up
  by a hard-hitting rhythm section. \n\nFor their show at the Hall of the 
 Above in Petaluma on April 11\, the Renegade Orchestra will present a revo
 lving set of music all based on the sounds of San Francisco…and the Bay 
 Area\, featuring pieces written by famous Bay Area rock bands or even just
  recorded in the Bay Area. These are classic tunes reimagined like Jeffers
 on Airplane’s Somebody to Love\, It’s a Beautiful Day’s White Bird\,
  and even some orchestral punk by the Dead Kennedys. \n\nAt this show\, t
 he Renegade Orchestra will present a comfortable\, but lively show featuri
 ng around 15 musicians\, all committed to having a relaxed and rocking tim
 e. If there is something you hate about orchestra concerts\, this is the o
 pposite.
LOCATION:Hall of the Above -located in the historic Sonoma County National
  Bank building.
URL:http://RenegadeOrchestra.com
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
