DESCRIPTION:Kearsley\, Sonoma’s renowned luxury linen and textile atelie
 r\, is relocating. In preparation\, the atelier has released its Kearsley 
 and Barbara Beckmann inventory at rare\, decisive pricing\, beginning at 5
 0% off.\n\nThe sale includes in-stock bed linens\, duvet covers\, coverlet
 s\, sheets\, pillowcases\, shams\, and outdoor pillows\, as well as fine f
 abrics by the yard for upholstery and drapery. Also available are hotel sa
 mple robes\, antique furniture\, a sleigh bed\, original artwork\, and rar
 e textile pieces seldom offered to the public.\n\nA broader selection is a
 vailable in-store\, including one-of-a-kind furnishings and collector-leve
 l pieces not listed online.\n\nKearsley is located through the Orchard Pla
 ce driveway entrance at Winery Sixteen 600\, and can also be accessed dire
 ctly from First Street West. The atelier is situated upstairs\, in the bac
 k of the beautiful yellow building.\n\nThis is a limited opportunity to ac
 quire exceptional design work from one of Sonoma’s most distinctive atel
 iers. Ideal for interior designers\, private clients\, collectors\, and th
 ose seeking truly special gifts.\n\nIn-store at 561 First Street West\, So
 noma\, and online at kearsleyhome.com April 1 through April 17\, while sel
 ections last.
LOCATION:Kearsley Sonoma Atelier
URL:https://kearsleyhome.com/collections/moving-sale
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
