DESCRIPTION:Tomato Plant Sale! Come to this one-day-only sale to get beau
 tiful\, locally-grown tomato plants -- grown from seed by the UC Master G
 ardeners of Napa County. ﻿\n\n25 varieties to choose from — newcomers
  & old favorites — you are sure to find the perfect tomato plants to add
  to your garden and your table. Heirloom and specially selected hybrids\, 
 such as: Early Girl\, Brandywine\, Black Krim\, Japanese Black Trifele\,
  Pink Berkeley Tie Dye\, Cherokee Green\, Captain Lucky\, Black Cherry\, S
 ungold\, Sunrise Bumblebee\, Napa Chardonnay\, Sweet Carneros Pink\, Amish
  Paste\, San Marzano II and more!﻿\n\nFind more information on this sale
 \, a list with descriptions of all of the varietals\, and growing tips: h
 ttps://ucanr.edu/site/uc-master-gardeners-napa-county/tomato-plant-sale-an
 d-education-day-event\n\n Saturday\, April 11\, 9am-until sold out! 1710 
 Soscol Ave\, Napa \\(just south of Central Valley Hardware\\).  $5 each. 
 Cash & checks only. \n\n﻿All proceeds benefit our Master Gardeners' edu
 cational programs for Napa County residents.
LOCATION:US Master Gardeners
URL:https://ucanr.edu/site/uc-master-gardeners-napa-county/tomato-plant-sa
 le-and-education-day-event
