BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Annual Art of Dessert 2026
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260411T173000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260411T200000
UID:260401FwaqX0mi7UOUKp0kWxU1ig
DESCRIPTION:Back to All Shows\n\nThe 23rd Annual Art of Dessert\n\nThe Art
  of Dessert is LBC’s biggest fundraising event of the year. Over the ye
 ars\, it has raised more than $8 million to help provide enrichment in the
  arts to over 1 million children\, families\, and educators. \n\nMuch anti
 cipated\, spirited\, and delicious\, The Art of Dessert features sumptu
 ous family-style dining\, exceptional Rodney Strong Wine Estates wines\, e
 ngaging entertainment\, a silent and live auction\, and\, of course\, deca
 dent desserts by the best bakers in the county! Bid on unique live auction
  items and enjoy lively entertainment and engaging speakers. Sonoma County
 ’s best fundraiser is a night to remember\, and your support will make a
  difference for over 50\,000 students\, teachers\, and families in the com
 ing year. \n\nWHY YOUR SUPPORT MATTERS \n\nThanks to your support\, Luther
  Burbank Center for the Arts is the North Bay’s premier arts nonprofit\,
  a vibrant gathering place providing world-class performances\, a wide var
 iety of community events\, and nationally-recognized education programs th
 at annually serve over 50\,000 students\, teachers\, and families. \n\nTic
 kets and more information coming soon! \n\nWhy Your Support Matters\n\nTha
 nks to your support\, Luther Burbank Center for the Arts is the North Bay
 ’s premier arts nonprofit\, a vibrant gathering place providing world-cl
 ass performances\, a wide variety of community events\, and nationally-rec
 ognized education programs that annually serve over 50\,000 students\, tea
 chers\, and families. \n\nTickets and more information coming soon! \n\nJo
 in the Fun – Join the Cause!\n\nThere are many ways to get involved with
  The Art of Dessert and support children\, teachers\, families\, and artis
 ts in our community\, even from home! \n\nApril 4 – 13\, 2026 \n\nOnline
