UID:2603296glTxHuhEEuh4VAAiqK-sw
DESCRIPTION:Join us at The MAC for the opening of: “The Wyeths: Three Ge
 nerations | Works from the Bank of America Collection”  Co-hosted by Ban
 k of America  Saturday\, April 11 | 5:00 PM to 7:00 PM  Representing one o
 f the most extraordinary collections of American artworks to ever be displ
 ayed in our region\, including paintings that travel rarely\, the exhibiti
 on will only be with us for five short months. Be there to celebrate with 
 us on its opening day. Enjoy a painted escape to the East Coast\, accompan
 ied by V. Sattui wines and hors d’oeuvres.  For three generations\, the 
 Wyeths have captured the imagination and admiration of a wide audience thr
 ough their works. Spanning more than 100 years of works from the early 190
 0s to present day\, it provides a comprehensive survey of works by N. C. W
 yeth\, one of America’s finest illustrators\; his son\, Andrew\, an impo
 rtant realist painter\; and Andrew’s son Jamie\, a popular portraitist. 
  COMP TICKETS: MAC Pack and Patrons\, secure your complimentary tickets by
  emailing Adrian@napavalleymuseum.org and obtaining a ticket confirmation.
  MAC Pack\, Patron and Members may purchase additional guest tickets at th
 e Member Price.
URL:https://www.facebook.com/events/25961222680173578/
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
