BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Overeaters Anonymous (OA) Newcomer Meeting
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260411T094500
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260411T101500
UID:2602125yHD_-QrWky-3xgGYG1IHg
DESCRIPTION:Is Food a Problem for You? You Are Not Alone.\n\nOvereaters An
 onymous \\(OA\\) is a fellowship of people who support each other in recov
 ering from compulsive eating and food behaviors. If you feel you have a pr
 oblem with food\, OA welcomes you—no matter what your background\, belie
 fs\, or eating habits. \n\nWe hold an in-person newcomer meeting on first
 \, second and fourth Saturdays of the month from 9:45 - 10:15 AM at ​Uni
 tarian Universalist Congregation of Marin\, 240 Channing Way\, San Rafael 
 CA 94903. Contact: Sue M. 415-298-6792​. You may view all North Bay OA 
 in-person and online meetings at https://www.northbayoa.org/meetings.html\
 n\nIn OA\, members experience spiritual\, emotional\, and physical recover
 y by practicing the Twelve Steps and living by their spiritual principles
 —one day at a time.\n\nOA is not a diet club or calorie-counting program
 .\n\nMembers have different plans of eating.\n\nOA does not endorse any sp
 ecific food plan. \n\nIf food is causing problems in your life\, you don
 ’t have to struggle alone. Recovery is possible\, and help is available.
 \n\nVisit: https://www.northbayoa.org/\n\nFind a meeting: https://www.nort
 hbayoa.org/meetings.html
LOCATION:Unitarian Universalist Congregation of Marin
URL:https://www.northbayoa.org/
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
