BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:KWMR's 'Cultivating Place' Live! with radio-host Jennifer Jewell
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260412T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260412T140000
UID:260328mJlJtr02bUe3Xs1Z4vMpxw
DESCRIPTION:Jennifer Jewell’s popular podcast "Cultivating Place\," expl
 ores ‘natural history and the human impulse to garden.” KWMR Community
  Radio is proud to air it Saturday mornings from 8-9 AM on the West Marin 
 airwaves\, and we are very excited to announce that we’ll be hosting Jen
 nifer Jewell in person for a live taping of her show! \n\nPlease join KWM
 R for “Cultivating Place LIVE\,” an interactive\, garden-focused event
  benefitting KWMR\, at The Dance Palace Community Center in Point Reyes St
 ation\, on Sunday\, April 12th.\n\nDoors open at 2 PM for mingling and a s
 eed swap with West Marin Climate Action. Bring your extra seeds and starts
  down\, to mix & match with fellow gardeners and cultivators…while enjoy
 ing snacks and local tea!\n\nThen at 3 PM\, when we’ll be doing a live t
 aping of Jennifer Jewell’s conversation with Rebecca Newburn - seed cons
 ervationist\, and co-founder of the Richmond Seed Lending Library. Stick a
 round after the talk for more mingling with fellow nature-enthusiasts. \n
 \nTickets are on sale at kwmr.org. This event is sliding scale\, $10-$50\,
  and all proceeds provide "seed funding" to fertilize KWMR’s upcoming Sp
 ring Pledge Drive\, happening April 18th through May 1st. Please choose th
 e ticket price that feels right for you\, or buy yours at the door! \n\nT
 hank you to our generous Event Sponsors: • Bolinas Hardware • Commonwe
 al New School • Gathering Thyme • Inverness Garden Club of West Marin 
 • Larner Seeds • Motel Inverness • Point Reyes Lavender Company.\n\n
 Thank you for your support of homegrown radio - see you on April 12th!
LOCATION:Dance Palace Community Center
URL:https://www.pressdemocrat.com/events/#/details/kwmr-s-cultivating-plac
 e-live-with-radio-host-jennifer-jewell/18442534/2026-04-12T14
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
