BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Crochet Innovations: Exploring Form
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260414T130000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260414T160000
UID:260328DysYSGih8kOVO8XdKATLDA
DESCRIPTION:Schedule\n\nTuesday\, April 14\, 2026 1:00 PM – 4:00 PM\n\nL
 ocation\n\nRoom 201\, Fiber Arts Studio\n\nExperience Level\n\nIntermediat
 e\n\nEvent Category: Fiber Arts\n\nAge\\(s\\)\n\n13\\+\n\nRegistration Cos
 t:\n\n$50\n\nMaterials:\n\nSee required list\n\nTotal Registration Cost:\n
 \n$50\n\nExplore sculptural crochet in this guided workshop. Learn expansi
 on\, contraction\, merging\; create small freeform pieces.\n\nAbout the Cl
 ass\n\nJoin us for an exploration of the innovative possibilities within c
 rochet! This workshop invites you to delve into the sculptural aspects of 
 the craft while creating freeform sculptures. Drawing inspiration from a r
 ich tradition\, you will be introduced to a variety of techniques that I
 ’ve learned and developed over the years in my own artistic practice. Gu
 ided throughout the process\, you will utilize essential materials such as
  yarn and crochet hook to learn the basics of expansion\, contraction\, el
 ongating\, merging corners\, and adding on. Whether for your own unique sc
 ulptures\, or incorporating into your mixed media projects\, by the end of
  the workshop you can expect to take home a few small finished pieces or w
 ork samples to inspire further creativity. A basic understanding of croche
 t is recommended.\n\nPlease Bring the Following to the Workshop:\n\nCroche
 t hook size 2.5\n\n2 skeins \\(different colors\\) of a Pima 100 cotton\, 
 wound and ready to stitch.\n\nPlease consider supporting Sonoma’s local 
 yarn shop Noma Knits. Students registered for Crochet Innovations will rec
 eive a discount when purchasing two skeins of Malabrigo Verano yarn which 
 is recommended for this workshop.
LOCATION:Sonoma Community Center
URL:https://sonomacommunitycenter.org/programs/crochet-innovations-explori
 ng-form/
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
