BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Small Wonders
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260414T110000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260414T170000
UID:260324VP5bzL3EkEOcyfE45GUlTA
DESCRIPTION:Call for Art: Small Wonders\n\nSome of the most exquisite beau
 ty can be captured in the smallest of images and objects: the iridescence 
 of a hummingbird in flight\, a millefiori paperweight\, Faberge eggs\, or 
 a miniature woven basket. These pieces are modest in size but powerful in 
 creativity and expression.\n\nHealdsburg Center for the Arts \\(HCA\\) inv
 ites artists to submit paintings\, original fine art prints\, collage\, mi
 xed media\, drawings\, fiber arts\, sculptures\, ceramics\, and jewelry fo
 r this exhibition.\n\nApplication Requirements:\n\n- Platform: All applica
 tions must be submitted via EntryThingy\n\n- Eligibility: Work must be ori
 ginal and completed within the past two years. Photos in the application m
 ust represent the actual work intended for exhibition.\n\n- Size/Weight: A
 rtwork must not exceed 12" x 12" unframed \\(144 sq in\\) or 196 sq in fra
 med. Maximum weight is 40 lbs.\n\n- Display: 2-D pieces must be securely w
 ired \\(no alligator clips\\). 3-D work must be stable\; artists are respo
 nsible for on-site assembly if required.\n\n- Sales: All work must be for 
 sale. HCA retains a 40% commission\; artists receive 60%. Please list reta
 il prices only.\n\nKey Dates:\n\n- Entry Deadline: May 10\, 2026 \\(9 PM\\
 )\n\n- Notification of Selection: By May 13\, 2026\n\n- Shipped Work Deadl
 ine: Wednesday\, May 27\, 2026 \\(must include pre-paid return label\\)\n\
 n- Hand-Delivery: Sunday\, May 31 \\(12–4 PM\\) and Monday\, June 1 \\(1
 1 AM–1 PM\\)\n\n- Exhibition Dates: June 4\, 2026 – July 19\, 2026\n\n
 - Opening Reception: Saturday\, June 6\, 2026 \\(4–6 PM\\)\n\n- Pick-up/
 Return Shipping: July 19 \\(12–4 PM\\) and July 20 \\(11 AM–1 PM\\)\; 
 shipping the week of July 20.\n\nEntry Fees:\n\n- Non-Members: $50 \\(1 en
 try\\)\, $55 \\(2 entries\\)\, $60 \\(3 entries\\). Includes a $60 yearly 
 supporter membership.\n\n- Current Members: $40 \\(1 entry\\)\, $45 \\(2 e
 ntries\\)\, $50 \\(3 entries\\).
LOCATION:Healdsburg Center for the Arts
URL:https://healdsburgcenterforthearts.org/small-wonders-2/
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Wildflower Preserve Hike at Van Hoosear
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260414T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260414T123000
UID:2603245vdIxEnTZEyqkeHS_ilDyA
DESCRIPTION:The Van Hoosear Wildflower Preserve is a 163-acre field on the
  lower slopes of Sonoma Mountain. Every year\, an extraordinary array of w
 ildflowers bursts forth in the fields with different species on display at
  different times of the spring. Thanks to the Goode family for sharing acc
 ess to the property and to SEC for co-managing it\, we will be leading one
  of the few hikes at the preserve this year. Don’t miss your chance and 
 join us to experience this fleeting spectacle. There is also a chance we w
 ill see song birds\, raptors\, coyotes\, and many butterflies.\n\nIt will 
 be a leisurely 2-mile hike with a brief uphill at the beginning. These hik
 es fill up fast\, so sign up early.
LOCATION:Van Hoosear Wildflower Preserve
URL:https://sonomamountain.org/upcoming-hikes-on-sonoma-mountain/
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
