BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Pizza-Making Class with Chef Bryan Jones\, supporting Sonoma Famil
 y Meal
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260416T170000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260416T193000
UID:260324YREaI0e5Mk-jM0Uzkchn6g
DESCRIPTION:Craft Pizza-Making Class with Chef Bryan Jones - April 16\n\n$
 100.00\n\nWe’re finally bringing pizza to the Sonoma Family Meal kitchen
 ! Join us and chef Bryan Jones for a cooking class on Thursday\, April 16t
 h to learn how to perfect the art of scratch pizza dough\, marinara\, and 
 mouthwatering toppings to satisfy all your senses.\n\nThe hands-on\, colla
 borative class will last 2.5 hours\, with time to enjoy your meal together
  at the end. Whether you’re a seasoned cook or just starting out\, this 
 class will offer a fun\, engaging learning environment\, while raising fun
 ds for Sonoma Family Meal’s free culinary job training and food-security
  programs.\n\nIf you haven’t been to the SFM Kitchen yet\, this class is
  also the perfect chance to visit and experience where the magic takes pla
 ce and how the work gets done.\n\nWHEN: Thursday April 16th\, 5-7:30pm WHE
 RE: SFM community kitchen\, 1370A Redwood Way\, Petaluma\n\nTHE MENU:\n\nS
 cratch Pizza Dough\n\nScratch Marinara Sauce\n\nMargherita Pizza\n\nHot Ho
 ney & Pepperoni Pizza\n\nBig Seasonal Salad will be served\n\nBYOB: Bring 
 Your Own Beverage\n\nIf you have a specific food allergy or have any quest
 ions about the menu\, please contact hannah@sonomafamilymeal.org.\n\nABOUT
  THE CHEF:\n\nBryan Jones takes the art of restaurant quality cuisine outs
 ide of the traditional restaurant kitchen and into evocative local spaces 
 and intimate environments. Offering boutique catering and private chef ser
 vices\, Bryan offers a culinary experience that’s creative\, custom and 
 designed from scratch for each menu and every singular occasion. \n\nAs a
  graduate of the California Culinary Academy in San Francisco\, Bryan brin
 gs over 20 years of experience in the kitchen to his craft. His approach t
 o food reflects a diverse restaurants background\, showcasing bold\, clean
  flavors and influences from a variety of cultures. \n\nAs the Executive 
 Chef at St. Francis Winery\, Bryan was the creative force behind the highl
 y rated food and wine pairing program at the winery\, where it was Zagat r
 ecommended and voted \\#1 restaurant by OpenTable diners in 2013 and 2015.
  He joined St. Francis winery in 2014 after ten years as Chef and General 
 Manager of the fig cafe and wine bar\, the sister restaurant of the girl a
 nd the fig. He has cooked in locations around the world\, including Garmis
 ch\, Germany\, Vail\, Colorado\, Santa Fe\, New Mexico and many other loca
 tions throughout the Bay Area. \n\nBryan uses this culinary history—and
  a natural curiosity for how experiences translate onto the palette—to c
 reate one-of-a-kind experiences in unique locations and private homes acro
 ss Wine Country\, and beyond.
LOCATION:Sonoma Family Meal Community Kitchen
URL:https://www.pressdemocrat.com/events/#/details/pizza-making-class-with
 -chef-bryan-jones-supporting-sonoma-family-meal/18357393/2026-04-16T17
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Drawing in Joy: Laughing with Life\, a Dance on Paper
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260416T173000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260416T200000
UID:260324VQaudcg2BEK6rkqJRtAg9g
DESCRIPTION:Schedule\n\nThursdays\, April 9 – 30\, 2026 5:30 PM – 8:00
  PM\n\nLocation\n\nRoom 208\n\nExperience Level\n\nAll Levels\n\nEvent Cat
 egories: Drawing & Painting\, Extended Classes\n\nAge\\(s\\)\n\n18 and old
 er\n\nRegistration Cost:\n\n$175\n\nMaterials Fee:\n\nSee Required List\n\
 nTotal Registration Cost:\n\n$175\n\nExpress joy through drawing. Build sk
 ills in sketching\, composition & landscapes. Boost focus\, creativity\, c
 onnection & well-being.\n\nAbout the Class\n\nWhen we feel a sense of joy\
 , it is natural to express that feeling from our body. We may use our voic
 e and sing\, we may dance\, and we may use our hands in creative expressio
 n. By drawing we leave a mark of that expression. This course is shaped wi
 th skill building exercises to improve eye-hand coordination with quick sk
 etching and gesture drawing and practices of learning to see how to abstra
 ct shapes of light and dark for developing strong compositions. We will fo
 cus on landscape imagery from photos and drawing from setups in the studio
 . Drawing outside of class will be encouraged but not required. There are 
 many health benefits from drawing such as: improvements in cognitive focus
 \, freedom of expression with your hands\, the satisfaction that comes fro
 m seeing the world in a different way\, the social camaraderie of acceptan
 ce in the studio\, and the joy of doing something with your hands.\n\nRequ
 ired Materials List\n\nA good size sketch book for multimedia\n\nNewsprint
  drawing pad \\(12” x 18” or 18” x 24”\\)\n\nBlack pencils\, 6B so
 ft\n\nCompressed charcoal sticks\, black and white\n\nEraser\, kneaded rub
 ber\n\nEraser\, white vinyl\n\nBlack felt pens
LOCATION:Sonoma Community Center
URL:https://sonomacommunitycenter.org/programs/drawing-in-joy/
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Sourdough Supper Club
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260416T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260416T210000
UID:260324J4gIw3QuGUeJwz08Occa4w
DESCRIPTION:**Chicky & Dumplins**\n\nApril 2\, 2026\, 6 to 9 pm\n\nJoin Ja
 mes Beard Award-winning cookbook author Sarah Owens for a night of making 
 luscious Chicken n' Dumplings with sourdough starter. If you've been looki
 ng for ways to use your starter besides baking\, this is for you! Sarah wi
 ll show you how to make an unconventional roux and light and fluffy dumpli
 ngs\, both with sourdough starter\, for a fun spin on this classic Souther
 n comfort food. To conclude the evening\, you will enjoy a sit-down meal o
 f a small appetizer\, chicken and dumplings\, salad\, and a light dessert.
  The chicken and dumplings include dairy and meat. One glass of locally pr
 oduced wine or NA beverage is included. \n\n**Galette Night**\n\nApril 16
 \, 2026 6 to 9 pm\n\nJoin James Beard Award-winning cookbook author Sarah 
 Owens for a night of galette making using a wholegrain sourdough pie crust
 . If you've been looking for ways to use your sourdough starter besides br
 ead\, this is for you! Sarah will show you how to roll out and fill a flak
 y\, wholesome pie crust made with spelt and sourdough starter\, perfect fo
 r both sweet and savory fillings. While the galettes are baking\, Sarah wi
 ll demonstrate how to mix the pie crust and provide you with a recipe to m
 ake at home. To conclude the evening\, you will enjoy a sit-down meal of s
 oup\, a savory galette\, salad\, and a light dessert. The soup and galette
  are vegetarian\, but both include dairy. One glass of locally produced wi
 ne or NA beverage is included.
LOCATION:Drewish Deli
URL:https://ritualfinefoods.com/products/sourdough-supper-club
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Small Wonders
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260416T110000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260416T170000
UID:260324DnQ8y4nvOU2aPCAf_IlS_A
DESCRIPTION:Call for Art: Small Wonders\n\nSome of the most exquisite beau
 ty can be captured in the smallest of images and objects: the iridescence 
 of a hummingbird in flight\, a millefiori paperweight\, Faberge eggs\, or 
 a miniature woven basket. These pieces are modest in size but powerful in 
 creativity and expression.\n\nHealdsburg Center for the Arts \\(HCA\\) inv
 ites artists to submit paintings\, original fine art prints\, collage\, mi
 xed media\, drawings\, fiber arts\, sculptures\, ceramics\, and jewelry fo
 r this exhibition.\n\nApplication Requirements:\n\n- Platform: All applica
 tions must be submitted via EntryThingy\n\n- Eligibility: Work must be ori
 ginal and completed within the past two years. Photos in the application m
 ust represent the actual work intended for exhibition.\n\n- Size/Weight: A
 rtwork must not exceed 12" x 12" unframed \\(144 sq in\\) or 196 sq in fra
 med. Maximum weight is 40 lbs.\n\n- Display: 2-D pieces must be securely w
 ired \\(no alligator clips\\). 3-D work must be stable\; artists are respo
 nsible for on-site assembly if required.\n\n- Sales: All work must be for 
 sale. HCA retains a 40% commission\; artists receive 60%. Please list reta
 il prices only.\n\nKey Dates:\n\n- Entry Deadline: May 10\, 2026 \\(9 PM\\
 )\n\n- Notification of Selection: By May 13\, 2026\n\n- Shipped Work Deadl
 ine: Wednesday\, May 27\, 2026 \\(must include pre-paid return label\\)\n\
 n- Hand-Delivery: Sunday\, May 31 \\(12–4 PM\\) and Monday\, June 1 \\(1
 1 AM–1 PM\\)\n\n- Exhibition Dates: June 4\, 2026 – July 19\, 2026\n\n
 - Opening Reception: Saturday\, June 6\, 2026 \\(4–6 PM\\)\n\n- Pick-up/
 Return Shipping: July 19 \\(12–4 PM\\) and July 20 \\(11 AM–1 PM\\)\; 
 shipping the week of July 20.\n\nEntry Fees:\n\n- Non-Members: $50 \\(1 en
 try\\)\, $55 \\(2 entries\\)\, $60 \\(3 entries\\). Includes a $60 yearly 
 supporter membership.\n\n- Current Members: $40 \\(1 entry\\)\, $45 \\(2 e
 ntries\\)\, $50 \\(3 entries\\).
LOCATION:Healdsburg Center for the Arts
URL:https://healdsburgcenterforthearts.org/small-wonders-2/
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
