DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260418T160000
UID:260404xi5AqJiEs0yaGI_tujrsrg
DESCRIPTION:“….Get ready for the super-entertaining sounds of local ba
 nd The Social Contractors. They totally rock\, in all the right ways…”
  - Argus-Courier\n\nJoin us after the Butter & Egg Days parade at the "Far
 mhouse Artisan Market Music Stage" (foot of B Street at the Petaluma River
  Turning Basin) for an afternoon of upbeat original rock and classic hits 
 from the 60s-90s (Beatles\, Hendrix\, Pink Floyd\, Tom Petty\, Police\, Do
 ors\, Steely Dan\, U2\, Men at Work\, and more)! \n\nThe Social Contracto
 rs will be performing with a special lineup including local "all stars" Tr
 avis Thayer (Cozy Cats\, Blue 7) on sax/keys/vocals\, Rob Neidel (Hyperdri
 ve Kittens) on bass\, Chris Oatman (The Receders) on drums\, and special g
 uest\, Robert Ramirez (Cozy Cats\, Mighty Groove) on percussion.\n\nWhethe
 r you like melodic vocals\, searing solos\, intriguing lyrics\, or just gr
 eat dynamic and danceable rhythms\, The Social Contractors won't disappoin
 t. \n\n**https://petalumadowntown.com/butter-eggs-parade.html**
LOCATION:Farmhouse Artisan Market Riverfront Stage
URL:https://petalumadowntown.com/butter-eggs-parade.html
