DESCRIPTION:**ART HATCHERY OPEN STUDIO**\n\n**Saturday\, April 18 \, 2026*
 *\n\n**12 pm – 5 pm**\n\n**Art Hatchery Studios**\n\n**401 7th street  
  ( between F & G streets)**\n\n**Petaluma\, Ca 94952**\n\nThe Art Hatcher
 y is a diverse group of Petaluma artists working across painting\, photogr
 aphy\, fiber art\, printmaking\, and mixed media. This is not a gallery—
 it’s a living\, working studio environment where creativity happens ever
 y day. During Open Studios\, visitors can step inside\, meet the artists\,
  and discover original work in an authentic\, approachable setting.\n\nThe
  Art Hatchery\, a historic brick chicken hatchery built in 1906\, has been
  converted into artist studios.  Artists in this collective include:\n\n
  **Lance Kuehne**: fine art photographer / https://lancekuehne.com/\n\n 
 **See See Lo**: painter / https://www.botzilla.com/see*see*lo.html\n\n **
 Nancy Lloyd**: oil painter / https://nancylloydart.com/\n\n**Joanne Tepper
 :** oil painter / https://joannetepper.com/\n\n **Andrea E Leland**: prin
 tmaker & painter / https://andrealeland.com/\n\n **Michele Rosett**: pain
 ter / https://michelerosett.squarespace.com/\n\n **Stephanie Sherratt**: 
 paper fabricator / https://www.instagram.com/paperfabricglitter/\n\n **Ha
 mish Hafter**: framer / owner of Edge Gallery\n\n **Phyllis Calvin-Thomas
 :** oil painter / https://www.phylliscalvinthomas.com/\n\n **Jim Thomas**
 : photographer / https://www.jimthomasphotography.com/
LOCATION:Petaluma Art Hatchery
URL:https://www.facebook.com/the.art.hatchery
