DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260418T110000
UID:2603177kflO_zxrkWj34S8H1gHpA
DESCRIPTION:**Ready to learn intermediate steps and technique?** Join on 
 on Saturday – Salsa Beginner Marin\n\nAre you a beginner who’s always 
 wanted to learn salsa? Salsa classes are designed to help you build a stro
 ng foundation. In this class\, you’ll learn the fundamental footwork\, p
 ractice the basic turns\, and understand the essential body movement that 
 will make you feel confident on the dance floor. This class is perfect for
  anyone ready to learn the techniques and foundational steps needed to sta
 rt their salsa journey.\n\nSalsa is fun\, and we make learning it stress-f
 ree! Our relaxed\, beginner-friendly class is the ideal starting point. Yo
 u don’t need a partner\, nor any dance experience!\n\nIn this class you 
 will learn:\n\nBasic directional steps that form the foundation of salsa.\
 n\nProper frame for comfortable and effective partner-work.\n\nSimple\, ea
 sy-to-remember turn patterns.\n\nGet ready to learn the fundamentals and h
 ave a great time!\n\n**Details:**\n\n**No partner necessary**—rotations 
 ensure everyone dances\n\nPlease wear **non-marking shoes** to protect t
 he floor\n\nArrive 10 minutes early\; warm up and settle in\n\n**When:** 
 Saturday\, 10:00 am – 11:00 am\n\n**Where:** 4140 Redwood Highway #8\, 
 San Rafael\, CA
LOCATION:4140 Redwood Highway #8\, San Rafael\, CA
URL:https://salsadancemarin.com/salsa-beginners-saturday/
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:GUIDE DOGS FOR THE BLIND'S GRADUATION CEREMONIES MELT HEARTS
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260418T133000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260418T143000
UID:260314td9tauzmK0q7RxFGsCuWMg
DESCRIPTION:Guide Dogs for the Blind \\(GDB\\) will celebrate its guide d
 og team graduates every other Saturday with public graduation ceremonies a
 t the organization’s campus in San Rafael. These touching public events 
 have inspired tears in even the most stoic audience members\, as graduatin
 g guide dog teams proudly take the stage. Families are welcome at the cere
 monies\, which honor the independence and companionship that GDB’s gui
 de dogs provide for GDB’s clients who are blind or visually impaired. T
 he events also allow GDB’s clients to meet the puppy raisers who cared 
 for their canine heroes prior to beginning formal training at GDB’s cam
 pus. Ceremonies also recognize recent graduates of GDB’s Orientation an
 d Mobility \\(O&M\\) Program\, K9 Buddy Program\, and Breeder Dog Program
 .\n\nAdmission is free\, and Kleenex will be provided. Pre-registered bus 
 groups are welcome. Public tours of the campus are offered on the days of 
 the ceremonies. Visit www.guidedogs.com for more information. Graduat
 ion events are also livestreamed at https://www.youtube.com/@gdb\\_offici
 al/streams.
LOCATION:Guide Dogs for the Blind
URL:https://www.guidedogs.com/about-guide-dogs-for-the-blind/graduations
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
