DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260419T180000
UID:260405D0Rhyk_SL0W-G4p0rZqzFA
DESCRIPTION:**Bingo Smokeout: Reefer Madness Edition**\n\nNumbers. Prizes.
  Elevated Vibes.\n\nOn **Sunday\, April 19th from 10AM – 6PM**\, step in
 to a high-energy twist on a classic favorite inside The Lounge at Mercy.\n
 \nThis isn’t your average bingo.\n\nThis is bingo—elevated.\n\nCards i
 n hand. Smoke in the air. Energy in the room.\n\nPlay through multiple bin
 go rounds throughout the day\, compete for prizes\, and stay locked into a
 n experience that blends cannabis culture with interactive gameplay from s
 tart to finish.\n\nYour ticket includes access to all bingo sessions\, one
  handcrafted herbal cocktail\, brand tastings\, exclusive product drops\, 
 and additional games and activations happening across the space.\n\nBetwee
 n rounds\, explore\, connect\, and keep the momentum going—this is a ful
 l-day experience built for 420 weekend.\n\nOne game. All day.\n\nLet the n
 umbers hit.\n\nThis is a 420-friendly interactive experience hosted inside
  our fully licensed cannabis consumption lounge\, where guests can enjoy r
 esponsibly while participating in gameplay\, tastings\, and activations. B
 ingo hits different here.\n\n**Ticket Tier**\n\n$25 — General Admission\
 n\nEntry to Bingo Smokeout 🎱\n\nIncludes access to all bingo rounds\, o
 ne herbal cocktail\, brand tastings\, games\, and product drops.\n\n21+ On
 ly | DCC # C12-0000420-LIC
LOCATION:The Lounge at Mercy
URL:https://www.themercylounge.com
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Free pipe-organ concert in Healdsburg April 19
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260419T170000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260419T180000
UID:2604016ekhz3xRBUCcd-dwL8XdFw
DESCRIPTION:Paul Blanchard\, the director of music for St. Paul's Episcopa
 l Church of Healdsburg\, plays a concert related to the Holy Trinity at 5 
 p.m. Sunday\, April 19. Blanchard will be seated at the church's Bigelow p
 ipe organ installed inside the church\, which is located at the corner of 
 East and Matheson Streets\, one block east of Healdsburg's downtown Plaza.
 \n\nAdmission is free. Donations to the church's building maintenance fund
  will be gratefully accepted.\n\nBlanchard will play these compositions: M
 arcello's Psalm 19 and Bohm's 3 settings of Vater unser in Himmelreich (Lo
 rd's Prayer)\; J.S. Bach's Vom Himmel Hoch and his Ascension by Messiaen's
  Priere du Christ (Ascension Suite\, No. IV)\; Thomas Fielding's Versets o
 n Veni Creator (w chanted verses)\, and Weckmann's O Lux Beata Trinitas.\n
 \nThose who cannot attend in person may watch the performance online by vi
 siting https://www.stpauls-healdsburg.org/sunday\\_organ\\_series.
LOCATION:St. Paul's Episcopal Church
URL:http://www.stpauls-healdsburg.org
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Sonoma County Philharmonic in concert - FANNY\, FLORENCE & SAM
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260419T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260419T160000
UID:260331J5KPanszsESh_HEoPdZTEQ
DESCRIPTION:**Norman Gamboa**\, conductor\n\n**Esther Rayo**\, soprano\n\n
 **SAMUEL COLERIDGE-TAYLOR** Idyll\, Op.44 \n\n**FANNY MENDELSSOHN** Hero 
 und Leander\n\n**FLORENCE PRICE** Symphony No. 1  \n\n**Join us for a pr
 ogram featuring three under- appreciated composers whose works are finally
  receiving the attention they deserve.**\n\n ♪ **Samuel Coleridge-Tayl
 or’s lovely *Idyll*** sets a reflective and poetic tone with its tender
  melodies and pastoral elegance.\n\n♪ **Fanny Mendelssohn’s dramatic 
 cantata\, *Hero und Leander***\, weaves a tragic Greek myth into music of
  passion and vivid orchestration.\n\n♪ **Florence Price’s groundbreak
 ing *Symphony No. 1*** blends classical forms with African American spir
 ituals and folk rhythms creating an iconic 20th century American masterpie
 ce. \n\n​**Come celebrate the breadth of orchestral music and its endur
 ing power to surprise\, delight\, and move the human spirit!**
LOCATION:Jackson Theater\, Sonoma Country Day School
URL:https://www.socophil.org/
