BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Benefit for Walker Creek Music Camp - An Evening of American Roots
  Music
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260422T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260422T210000
UID:260331RYdZzu5CQUaLTfSY20D12A
DESCRIPTION:**Walker Creek Music Camp Presents Teacher Concert Series IV**
  **Benefit Concert Celebrating American Roots Music**\n\nThe concert suppo
 rts Walker Creek Music Camp’s mission to provide world-class music educa
 tion and expand access to traditional roots music through classes\, youth 
 programs\, and scholarships.\n\nThe evening will feature these outstanding
  faculty and alumni performing bluegrass\, old-time\, jazz\, and swing:\n\
 n**Walker Creek All-Stars** A “supergroup” of current and former instr
 uctors featuring: Yoseff Tucker (guitar)\, Tod Livingston (dobro)\, Bethan
 y Raine Sorkey (bass)\, Paul Shelasky (fiddle)\, Ryan Breen (banjo)\, and 
 Tom Bekeny (mandolin).\n\n**Hildaland** A duo blending Scottish and Americ
 an traditions featuring fiddler Louise Bichan and mandolin virtuoso Ethan 
 Setiawan.\n\n**Pacific Drive** A high-energy bluegrass band formed at Walk
 er Creek Music Camp featuring Dana Frankel\, David Thiessen\, Jesse Fichma
 n\, Helen Foley\, and Sam Reed.\n\n**About Walker Creek Music Camp** Found
 ed in 2013\, Walker Creek Music Camp is a California nonprofit dedicated t
 o teaching\, preserving\, and celebrating American roots music. The camp o
 ffers world-class instruction for students of all ages and hosts sessions 
 twice each year at Walker Creek Ranch Conference Center.\n\nThe camp’s *
 *Music & More (M&M’s)** youth program provides tuition-free instruction 
 for children ages 6–13\, along with scholarships and work-trade opportun
 ities that help make music education accessible to all.\n\n**More informat
 ion:** **walkercreekmusiccamp.org**
LOCATION:Sebastopol Community Cultural Center
URL:https://www.walkercreekmusiccamp.org
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
