 rson body responsible for governing the library. Commissioners are appoint
 ed by the cities in Sonoma County and the county Board of Supervisors. The
  commission establishes policy\; sets goals and objectives\; hires and eva
 luates the director\; establishes and monitors the annual budget\; and exe
 rcises such other powers\, consistent with the law to foster the effective
  use and management of the library. The commission generally meets monthly
 \, with additional special meetings as needed. Meetings are open to the pu
 blic and recordings are accessible online through
