SUMMARY:Painting Flora and Fauna in Watercolor
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260424T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260424T130000
UID:260211c8GrZ5ySRkeXGK4Kjx19Yg
DESCRIPTION:Schedule\n\nFridays\, March. 20- April 24\, 2026 10:00 AM – 
 1:00 PM\n\nLocation\n\nRoom 208\n\nExperience Level\n\nAll Levels\n\nDrawi
 ng & Painting\n\nAge\\(s\\)\n\n18 and older\n\n$275 – Registration Cost 
 $25 – Materials Fee $300 – Total Registration CostIn this six-week cou
 rse\, participants will learn a unique approach to watercolor\, intended t
 o alleviate the frustration that many experience when learning this beauti
 ful yet challenging medium.\n\nAbout the Class\n\nIn this six-week course\
 , participants will learn a unique approach to watercolor\, intended to al
 leviate the frustration that many experience when learning this beautiful 
 yet challenging medium. We will focus on strengthening one’s observation
 al drawing skills\, giving the artist a foundation off of which to build t
 heir paintings in a step-by-step layering process that trains the artist t
 o see value and color. Our subject matter will be flora and fauna – a sa
 mpling of plants and animals. These subjects are great for beginners and e
 xperienced artists alike\; their organic shapes make them forgiving drawin
 g subjects\, but their beauty can be a muse for life.  Instructor Hannah 
 Day is a passionate nature lover and watercolorist and will share her uniq
 ue approach to rendering botanicals and animal portraits in watercolor. Th
 is class will work both from photographs and from life\, practicing observ
 ational drawing in addition to watercolor technique. With six class sessio
 ns\, participants will have the opportunity to develop their skills and bu
 ild muscle memory with a medium that often feels like it has a mind of its
  own.  This class is open to artists of all skill levels. All materials a
 re provided.
LOCATION:Sonoma Community Center
URL:https://sonomacommunitycenter.org/programs/painting-flora-and-fauna/
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Gary Owen: No Hard Feelings Tour
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260424T200000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260424T200000
UID:260129v_wyNYXmIku7uzDOynnlgg
DESCRIPTION:Gary Owen has been entertaining audiences for more than two de
 cades with his sharp observational humor and fearless storytelling. Known 
 for his unapologetic\, rule-defying style\, his material draws from his pe
 rsonal life\, time in the military\, and the everyday absurdities that con
 nect people across backgrounds. With a fanbase that has grown by the milli
 ons in recent months and continues to surge across social media\, Owen’s
  reach has cemented his place as one of the most in-demand touring comedia
 ns today.\n\nBeyond stand-up\, Owen has appeared in a wide range of featur
 e films and television. He continues to write\, produce\, and perform his 
 own groundbreaking comedy specials. In addition to his on-stage and on-scr
 een work\, Owen hosts his own podcast\, \\#GetSome with Gary Owen.\n\nAges
  12\\+ Recommended\n\nVIP 1: Gary Owen VIP Meet & Greet Package\n\nPremium
  Seat Ticket\n\nMeet & Greet with Gary Owen\n\nPhoto with Gary Owen\n\nCom
 memorative VIP Laminate\n\nExclusive Autographed Merchandise Item\n\nVIP 2
 : Gary Owen VIP Merchandise Package\n\nPremium Seat Ticket\n\nExclusive Au
 tographed Merchandise Item\n\n\\*No artist participation
LOCATION:Luther Burbank Center for the Arts
URL:https://lutherburbankcenter.org/event/gary-owen-26/
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
