BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Emergence - Spring Through the Eyes of the Artists
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260424T110000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260424T160000
UID:26040170b-uefVakWZt4nujNxkPw
DESCRIPTION:"Emergence" brings together the Artists of Fulton Crossing to 
 explore what Spring means to their creative lives. Spring is more than a s
 eason. It's a metaphor. It's renewal\, risk\, color\, thawing\, blooming\,
  awakening\, and sometimes even struggles. The public is invited to enjoy 
 this free Art exhibit and to take time to wander through the artists studi
 os and gallery spaces. Meet the artists at our opening reception March 21s
 t. Upcoming Art Workshops: March 21: Painting Easter Cookies. April 18: Ci
 gar Box Collage. May 16: Succulent Garden Centerpiece. Make treasures to b
 ring home. All ages welcome. Materials provided. E-mail Brenda at nanaspre
 ttypaper@outlook.com for preregistration and workshop info.
LOCATION:Fulton Crossing art gallery
URL:https://creativesonoma.org/event/emergence-spring-through-the-eyes-of-
 the-artists/
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:INTO THE LIGHT: Light-filled aintings by Katy Boggs
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260424T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260424T170000
UID:260330VKaOrtZwnkyhBgghISY4AA
DESCRIPTION:Katy's paintings are an exploration of light—how it shapes f
 orm\, reveals color\, and defines what we see.\n\n"I am drawn to moments w
 here light is felt as much as seen: filtering through dense leaves\, tower
 ing in the crowns of trees\, glinting off cresting waves\, or softening in
 to the quiet glow of a sunset. Light is everywhere\; without it\, there is
  no seeing. Beyond its physical presence\, it also carries a deeper resona
 nce as a symbol of hope. In a time of uncertainty\, this work seeks to bri
 ng light into the image\, both visually and metaphorically."\n\nReception:
  April 25\, 4 to 6 pm.
LOCATION:Sebastopol Gallery
URL:http://sebastopolgallery.com
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Intermediate Salsa with Tyler
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260424T183000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260424T193000
UID:260319udwN7XbiG0aPLwRJ_Qu-LA
DESCRIPTION:Ready to learn intermediate steps and technique?\n\nAre you a 
 salsa dancer who has the basics down but is ready to add more? Our Interme
 diate Salsa Class with Tyler is designed to help you transform your dancin
 g moves. In this class\, you’ll go beyond the basics to learn intricate 
 footwork\, enhance your leading and following skills\, and master the body
  movement that will make you shine on the dance floor. This class is for a
 nyone ready to learn the techniques and intermediate steps needed to take 
 their dancing to the next level.\n\nYou’ll learn intermediate dancing te
 chniques that will help you:\n\nExpress yourself with sharper footwork and
  styling.\n\nMaster complex turn patterns and combinations.\n\nStrengthen 
 your lead and follow for seamless\, connected dancing.\n\nAdapt to differe
 nt partners and music with ease on the social dance floor.\n\nWhat to Expe
 ct: Instructor Tyler blends a fun\, supportive atmosphere with structured
  lessons\, so you’re always challenged but never overwhelmed. Helping yo
 u progress steadily while keeping the joy of salsa front and center.\n\nDe
 tails:\n\nNo partner necessary—rotations ensure everyone dances.\n\nPlea
 se wear non-marking shoes to protect the floor.\n\nArrive 10 minutes ear
 ly to warm up and get settled.\n\nWhen: Fridays\, 6:30 PM – 7:30 PM\n\n
 Instructor: Tyler Crandall\n\nWhere: 4140 Redwood Highway \\#8\, San Raf
 ael\, CA
LOCATION:4140 Redwood Highway #8 San Rafael
URL:https://www.pressdemocrat.com/events/#/details/intermediate-salsa-with
 -tyler/17624477/2026-04-24T18
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
