BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Fireside Chat with Sally Kohn - No Hate
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260424T173000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260424T190000
UID:2603196_omkFZg4kaGqev2kRqk4Q
DESCRIPTION:A fireside chat with Sally Kohn and Martin Gobbee- Moderator. 
   Sally a member of the queer community\, is a nationally recognized telev
 ision commentator\, writer and executive presence coac working iwth top ex
 ecutives and political leaders.  With her missage of connection and compas
 sion for all\, Sally is an in-demand speaker worldwide. In fun and informa
 tive talks\, filled with powerful personal stories and mind-blowing resear
 ch\, Sally helps teams and communities move past conflict to find their co
 mmon ground.  She leaves audiences feeling more empowered\, hopeful and in
 spired.  Sally's first book\, THE OPPOSITE OF HATE was published in April 
 2018.  She has three TED talks that have been viewed more than 6 million t
 imes. Moderator Martin Gobbee is a local business Manager in hospitality\,
  and a member of the Wake UP Sonoma Board. He and Sally have been friends 
 for many years\, and the two are having a reunion on stage with this fires
 ide chat.  He has a BA in history and a Master of Fine arts in acting from
  Brandeis University.
LOCATION:Sebastiani Theatre
URL:https://mynorthbaytickets.ticketsauce.com/e/fireside-chat-with-sally-k
 ohn-no-hate?aff=cityspark
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Callie Watts
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260424T000000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260424T000000
UID:260331MtOyA-xh_0-pTJi2MB6eFg
DESCRIPTION:Callie Watts is a singer/songwriter from Northern California w
 ho was raised on classical music\, The Beatles and The Beach Boys before d
 iscovering Joni Mitchell\, Elton John\, Stevie Wonder\, Paul Simon\, Billy
  Joel\, Carole King\, and all the great writers of the ’60s and 70’s w
 ho have influenced her sound and writing style. After graduating high scho
 ol\, Callie began playing and performing solo\, as well as in local and ba
 y area bands of different genres. She’s played blues with Eric Lindell a
 nd the Reds\, funky soul with Phatty\, and jazz/swing with Savoy Swingers 
 along with many other various projects. Callie has taken turns throughout 
 her career as a keyboardist\, guitarist\, writer\, and lead/backing vocali
 st\, and she’s currently a member of the dynamic Sonoma County funk rock
  band Burrows and Dilbeck\, having joined in 2010 as part of the former ba
 nd Frobeck. Over time\, she’s had the honor of opening for acts such as 
 Bootsy Collins\, Elvin Bishop\, Huey Lewis and The News\, War\, Ozomatli\,
  Bill Champlin\, Booker T\, and the B52s. Callie continues to perform freq
 uently as an acoustic solo artist\, focusing on developing a core audience
  and a buzz for her original material. Come hang out and listen at venues 
 such as Aroma Roasters\, Rincon Valley Tap Room and Bottle Shop\, and Hopm
 onk Tavern.
LOCATION:HopMonk Tavern
URL:https://www.bandsintown.com/e/108008889?app_id=pkvts0on0m&came_from=28
 7&utm_medium=api&utm_source=partner_api&utm_campaign=event
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
