BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Reto Naturalista Urbano (Urban Naturalist Challenge) en Español
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260425T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260425T170000
UID:260404bBO_x7Yf5EyX2MmYfVOy-Q
DESCRIPTION:Join staff from Sugarloaf Ridge and Jack London State Parks fo
 r a bioblitz **in Spanish** as part of the 2026 City Nature Challenge. \n
 \nA bioblitz is a period of biological exploration aimed at cataloging wil
 dlife within a specific area. For this outing\, we will use the iNaturalis
 t mobile app during a 4.25-mile hike along the Vista Loop. If you are unfa
 miliar with iNaturalist—or if you haven't logged an observation recently
 —this is your chance!  Be sure to download the app to your phone or oth
 er mobile device before arriving at the park\, and ensure your battery is 
 100% charged.\n\nThe group will meet at the White Barn parking area. We wi
 ll traverse sections of various trails featuring diverse habitats\, coveri
 ng a maximum distance of 4.25 miles with an elevation gain of approximatel
 y 800 feet. Registration requires a $5 deposit for adults\, which will be 
 refunded on-site on the day of the event unless you choose to donate it. M
 inors under 18 can attend for free but must be accompanied by a parent or 
 legal guardian. Due to the route and the nature of this activity\, it is n
 ot recommended for children under 10 years of age. Parking—typically $10
 —is free for this event. Free transportation is available for families i
 n need (within a 20-mile radius of the park).\n\nPlease wear footwear suit
 able for rocky or slippery trails\, and bring sun protection\, at least on
 e liter of water per person\, and a snack. We invite you to bring a magnif
 ying glass\, a plant or flower identification guide\, or binoculars. If yo
 u use a mobile app\, ensure your device's battery is 100% charged.\n\nFor 
 more information\, please email senderos@sonomaecologycenter.org or call M
 ario (707-387-4087 on Thursdays and Saturdays) or Alma (707-247-5767\, Tue
 sday through Saturday).\n\nThe City Nature Challenge\, April 24 to April 2
 7\, 2026\, is a friendly competition between "cities" to see who submits t
 he most wildlife observations\, who finds the greatest diversity of specie
 s\, and who engages the highest number of participants. Learn more about t
 he City Nature Challenge (you can read the page in Spanish by selecting th
 e language from the menu at the bottom of the webpage) or check out the Su
 garloaf Project.\n\nAccessibility: The White Barn parking area features a 
 designated space for vehicles displaying a disabled parking placard\, a po
 rtable restroom\, and a drinking water spigot. There is no cell phone serv
 ice in this area. There is a paved road approximately 200 meters long lead
 ing from the White Barn to the trailhead for the Lower Bald Mtn Trail. The
  Lower Bald Mtn Trail is a single-track path that is not accessible to whe
 elchairs or strollers. This dirt and gravel trail features multiple switch
 backs and climbs approximately 500 feet in elevation before connecting wit
 h the Bald Mtn Trail. The Bald Mtn Trail is a paved fire road that connect
 s the Lower Bald Mtn Trail to the Vista Trail. The Vista Trail is a single
 -track path with an elevation gain of at least 213 meters (700 feet). It f
 eatures at least two small seasonal stream crossings\, at least two sectio
 ns with steps\, and multiple steep\, slippery stretches. This trail connec
 ts with the Grey Pine Trail. Grey Pine Trail is a firebreak featuring a se
 asonal water crossing\, which can be traversed using a wooden plank as a b
 ridge. Continuing past Grey Pine\, Meadow Trail is an unpaved firebreak th
 at is relatively flat\, though not officially ADA-compliant. Meadow Trail 
 ends next to the Robert Ferguson Observatory\, just a few meters from the 
 White Barn parking lot.\n\nVisit https://sec.regfox.com/senderos26-cnc for
  registration and more information.
LOCATION:Sugarloaf Ridge State Park
URL:https://sec.regfox.com/senderos26-cnc
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Primaveras 2026: Climate Justice ~ Justicia Climática
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260425T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260425T160000
UID:260404OPyf9X4tnk-6h83lajawGw
DESCRIPTION:Primaveras es una celebración alegre que honra la riqueza y d
 iversidad de las diásporas Latinx y Comunidades de habla hispana. La Bibl
 ioteca de Novato Sur se enorgullece de su colaboración con organizaciones
  locales para crear iniciativas comunitarias que son relevantes culturalme
 nte y que reflejan las historias\, tradiciones\, y experiencias de nuestra
 s comunidades. Primaveras encarna la renovación\, crecimiento\, y sobre t
 odo\, la resiliencia de nuestras comunidades. Este año continuamos nuestr
 a colaboración con la Alianza Asiática Americana de Marín para celebrar
  juntes nuestra resiliencia y amor por la comunidad y los libros.\n\n~\n\n
 Primaveras is a joyful celebration that honors the richness and diversity 
 of Latinx diasporas and Spanish-speaking communities. The South Novato Lib
 rary proudly partners with local organizations to create culturally releva
 nt\, community-driven initiatives that reflect the stories\, traditions\, 
 and experiences of our communities. Primaveras embodies renewal\, growth\,
  and\, above all\, the resilience that defines our communities. This year 
 we are continuing our partnership with the Asian American Alliance of Mari
 n to celebrate together our resilience and our love for community and book
 s.
LOCATION:Marin Library: South Novato
URL:https://www.pressdemocrat.com/events/#/details/primaveras-2026-climate
 -justice-justicia-clim-tica/18508302/2026-04-25T10
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Stand-up + Improv = STANDPROV | Downtown Santa Rosa Good Times
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260425T200000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260425T220000
UID:260404Iqn37HEk40iNmApmEF2izA
DESCRIPTION:Get ready for a night of hilarious stand-up comedy and spontan
 eous improv at STANDPROV in Downtown Santa Rosa - it's gonna be a blast!\n
 \nStand-up + Improv = STANDPROV | Downtown Santa Rosa Good Time\n\nTake pa
 rt in a truly unique comedy experience! Equal parts standup and improvisat
 ional comedy\, StandProv electrifies audiences who enjoy spontaneous acts 
 of comedic re-interpretation.\n\nWith a blend aging like only the finest o
 f wines (four years)\, the StandProv concoction mixes stand-up comedy and 
 improv sourced from the best of Northern California comedians and improvis
 ers. StandProv frankensteins together the best parts of standup and improv
  comedy. Standup comedians perform their most time-tested bits\, which the
 n become the inspiration for a cast of improvisers to build out characters
 \, scenes\, and premises. Pairing non-stop entertainment with good vibes d
 istills the balanced portmanteau commonly referred to in layman's terms as
  StandProv .\n\nFeaturing premier Bay Area comedians and improvisers\, Sta
 ndProv offers a uniquely familiar performance experience to fans of standu
 p\, improv\, and experimental art-form fusions alike!\n\nApril's performer
 s include: - Marcus Peverill - Scott Powers - Brendan Caskey - Gina Maycli
 n - Josh Jobrack - Katie Lindsey - Rachel Pyle\n\nHosted By:\n\nFranco Tev
 ini\n\nA talented standup comedian and host of StandProv \, Franco perform
 s digestible bits of surreal\, elevated slice-of-life comedy.\n\nJeremy Le
 ssnau\n\nA Sonoma county based improvisational comedian/musician\, who co-
 hosts StandProv as equal parts passion-project and court-ordered community
  service.\n\nIf you're looking for a memorable night of rofl-worthy laught
 er\, check out StandProv at Barrel Proof Lounge in downtown Santa Rosa\, S
 aturday\, April 25th!\n\nVIP TABLES NOW AVAILABLE! Snag a table for 4 with
  preferred seating\, your own private call button to summon service\, and 
 your first round of drinks (or a bottle of wine) for only $95!\n\n21+ Door
 s @7/Show @8 $15adv / $20door\n\n"Equal parts standup and improvisational 
 comedy\, StandProv electrifies audiences who enjoy a laugh of any kind"\n\
 nCheck out **www.BarrelProofLounge.com** for all sorts of good times ahe
 ad!
LOCATION:Barrel Proof Lounge
URL:https://www.eventbrite.com/e/stand-up-improv-standprov-downtown-santa-
 rosa-good-times-tickets-1986559411677?aff=oddtdtcreator
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
