DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260425T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260425T210000
UID:260324G-kN7vm610eXGLeeMPogPg
DESCRIPTION:Cinnabar Theater presents The Christians by Lucas Hnath\n\nA p
 owerful\, thought-provoking drama about faith\, conviction\, and the cost 
 of standing by your beliefs.\n\nWhen a beloved megachurch pastor delivers 
 a sermon that challenges a core doctrine\, his congregation is thrown into
  turmoil. What follows is an intimate and gripping exploration of belief\,
  doubt\, leadership\, and community—inviting audiences to wrestle with b
 ig questions that linger long after the final moment on stage.\n\n• Warr
 en Theater\, Sonoma State University (Ives Hall)\, 1801 East Cotati Ave\, 
 Rohnert Park\, CA 94928\n\n• April 10–26\, 2026\n\n• Fridays & Satur
 days at 7:30 PM | Sundays at 2:00 PM\n\n• Special Talkback Post Show: Su
 nday\, April 19\n\nDirected by Nathan Cummings and featuring a stellar cas
 t\, this minimalist\, emotionally resonant production is recommended for m
 ature audiences.\n\nTickets: cinnabartheater.org
LOCATION:Warren Theater\, Sonoma State University (Ives Hall)\,
URL:https://cinnabartheater.org/show/thechristians/
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Calming the Restless Mind
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260425T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260425T150000
UID:260324BWwB_SyD8UKDC3EGBmRLyg
DESCRIPTION:with Howard Cohn\n\nEveryone wants to be calm and peaceful. Re
 stlessness and agitation can arise when the mind is unsettled\, the heart 
 is reactive\, and our perception of the present moment is unclear. During 
 this day together\, we will explore ways of steadying the heart and mind s
 o that calm in the present moment becomes more accessible\, insight devel
 ops naturally\, and the heart softens.\n\nDuring this daylong\, we will dr
 aw on the Four Foundations of Mindfulness—being mindful of and sensitive
  to our bodies—beginning with the sensations of breathing\, and expandin
 g to include other physical sensations. We will explore how to feel pleasu
 re more fully without trying to make it last\, and how to more easily acco
 mmodate unpleasant experiences without becoming overwhelmed or reactive. W
 e will also practice recognizing and working with our emotions\, while lea
 rning how to relate to our thoughts more kindly and skillfully rather than
  being so easily carried away by them.
LOCATION:Spirit Rock Meditation Center
URL:https://www.pressdemocrat.com/events/#/details/calming-the-restless-mi
 nd/18363181/2026-04-25T10
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
