BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Inspire Napa Valley Event Support Alzheimer's and Dementia Researc
 h
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260426T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260426T100000
UID:260309h1aPiFnU_kaxasTOjgQFcA
DESCRIPTION:The seventh annual Inspire Napa Valley will take place from Fr
 iday\, April 24 – Sunday\, April 26 in Napa Valley. Hosted by Kerrin L
 az\, founder of K. LAZ WINE COLLECTION\, the wine community and beyond to
  raise funds and awareness to advance Alzheimer’s and dementia research
  nationally and enhance local care and support services for impacted fami
 lies. Since its inception in 2017\, the event has raised over $9 milli
 on for these vital efforts. This impactful event continues to unite win
 e industry leaders and enthusiasts to raise awareness\, spark change\, a
 nd secure national funding for an incredible cause. Don't miss out on 
 this inspiring weekend that combines the best of Napa Valley with a commi
 tment to making a difference!Events include:\n\nFriday\, April 24 | VIP We
 lcome Dinner – The Best of Oakville\n\n5:30 PM | Gamble Estates\, Oakvil
 le\, CA\n\nAn exclusive evening\, The Best of Oakville\, brings together e
 ight of the region’s best wineries as co-hosts\, sharing their stories a
 nd wines\, from rare library selections to current releases. The experienc
 e is paired with a wine country feast led by Napa Valley’s own Chef Sean
  Massey and joined in the kitchen by some of wine country’s leading vint
 ners\, winemakers\, growers\, and industry icons. This intimate gathering 
 captures the spirit of true wine country hospitality.\n\nThe wineries incl
 ude Dalla Valle Vineyards\, Gamble Estates\, Harlan Estate\, Opus On\, Scr
 eaming Eagle\, Tench Vineyards\, VHR – Vine Hill Ranch\, FUTO\n\nSaturda
 y\, April 25 | VIP Alzheimer’s Research Update & Wine Tasting Seminar: D
 eep Dive Into Oakville’s Best\n\n10 AM | The Culinary Institute of Ameri
 ca at Greystone\, St. Helena\, CA\n\nFollowing an Alzheimer’s and dement
 ia research update from Inspire Napa Valley’s Scientific Advisors\, incl
 uding Gates Ventures’ Senior Director of Health & Life Sciences\, Farhad
  Imam\, guests will enjoy an in-depth exploration of six of Oakville’s m
 ost exceptional wines\, led by a distinguished panel including Antonio Gal
 loni\, founder of Vinous\, and Ray Isle\, Executive Wine Editor of Food & 
 Wine.\n\nIncluded for VIP guests. A limited number of seats are available 
 for main event guests.\n\nSaturday\, April 25 | Grand Wine Tasting\, Recep
 tion\, Dinner & Auction\n\n5 PM | Louis Martini Winery\, St. Helena\, CA\n
 \nEnjoy the walk-around Grand Tasting featuring more than 35 of California
 ’s most iconic wineries\, alongside a selection of exciting rising star 
 producers\, followed by a festive wine country dinner and Inspire Napa Val
 ley’s signature live auction and paddle raise.\n\nSunday\, April 26 | VI
 P Farewell Brunch\n\n10 AM | Ad Hoc \\+ Addendum Garden\n\nA farewell brun
 ch featuring Chef Thomas Keller’s Ad Hoc fried chicken and waffles\, alo
 ngside Bouchon seasonal dishes and a classic bloody mary and mimosa bar.
LOCATION:Louis Martini Winery
URL:https://www.inspirenapavalley.org/
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Por la Luz de la Luna: a Mexican Ballet
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260426T130000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260426T150000
UID:260306qfHBVLo0pk60kiZcU2H5fg
DESCRIPTION:This original ballet libretto was inspired by award-winning au
 thor and arts activist Aida Salazar’s story of her great-aunt\, Jovita V
 aldovinos\, who fought for religious freedom in Mexico’s Cristero War in
  the 1930s. *Por la Luz de la Luna* brings a fictional account of Jovita
 ’s story to life\, weaving history\, mythology\, and family legacy into 
 a powerful theatrical experience while celebrating her heroism. As one of 
 the few Mexican-themed ballets in history\, it creates a space for dancers
  of all backgrounds to portray Latina/o characters\, highlighting unique s
 tories and honoring Mexican and Mexican-American heritage on stage. Set to
  20th-century Mexican classical music by composers such as Carlos Chávez 
 and José Pablo Moncayo\, the ballet is brought to life through striking s
 ets and Aztec-inspired costumes designed by visual artist PEMEX. It premie
 red on April 9\, 2016\, at the Sebastiani Theatre and continues to be a hi
 ghlight of the company’s repertory.
LOCATION:Sebastiani Theatre
URL:https://www.sonomadance.org/tickets
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Wood Engraving - 2 Day Intensive Workshop
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260426T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260426T150000
UID:260216vNMSiZQbM0-gSESFUbkc3w
DESCRIPTION:This two-day workshop introduces the art and practice of wood 
 engraving. The hard woods used to make wood engraving blocks are type-high
  \\(.918”\, the height of metal type\\) and are cut across the grain rat
 her than parallel to it like wood cuts. These durable end-grain blocks all
 ow for extensive detail. The tools used are gravers \\(or burins\\) that a
 re different than the gouge tools used for wood cuts. This versatile form 
 of printmaking requires little space and minimal equipment and is perfect 
 for a small home studio.\n\nDay 1: We will start with a brief history of w
 ood engraving including its long relationship to letterpress printing\, an
 d we will study examples of period and contemporary wood engravings. Stude
 nts will begin with a sampler block to explore the effects of various too
 ls\, proof the block on the press\, and transfer a design onto another blo
 ck to consider the approach for their first engraving.\n\nDay 2: Student
 s will learn how to sharpen their gravers and continue to engrave their bl
 ocks. We will become familiar with basic use of the Vandercook SP-15 cylin
 der press to ink and proof the block and troubleshoot issues when printing
 . Printing an edition of a block will be discussed\, and those wanting to 
 contribute a print to the workshop portfolio are encouraged to do so. Stud
 ents will leave the workshop with the skills to master the graver tool to 
 create intricate prints\, a value test block for future reference\, an ins
 tructive handout\, a block to edition\, and a portfolio of workshop prints
 .\n\nLevel: Beginner – no previous experience necessary\n\nIncludes $50 
 materials fee\, which covers \\#3 elliptical tint tool and two 3”x 4” 
 end-grain maple blocks\\)\n\nINSTRUCTOR\n\nColleen Dwire initially learned
  wood engraving in a workshop with American Master John DePol and has been
  practicing for over thirty years. She exhibits her prints internationally
 . Colleen is an elected member of the Society of Wood Engravers \\(UK\\) a
 nd serves as Secretary and Exhibitions Officer for Wood Engravers’ Netwo
 rk \\(USA\\) and as a board member of North Bay Letterpress Arts. Learn mo
 re at www.colleendwire.com and follow on colleendwire.bsky.social.
