BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Passport to Dry Creek Valley
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260426T110000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260426T160000
UID:251222Mf6QtecFuUufTz-zliy6tQ
DESCRIPTION:Passport to Dry Creek Valley Public Event 11 a.m.-4 p.m. • 2
 1 & Older Only • No Children or Pets Allowed Set sail for one of Sonoma 
 County's most beloved wine weekends - Passport to Dry Creek Valley! This s
 pring celebration brings together more than 50 wineries for three days of 
 incredible wine\, food and live entertainment. Explore the beauty of Dry C
 reek Valley\, where multigenerational winemaking families craft world-clas
 s wines with passion\, purpose and a touch of magic. Make Dry Creek Vineya
 rd your first port of call! Our legendary pirate-themed bash is a Passport
  tradition\, complete with rollicking sea shanties from The SeaDogs \\(vot
 ed Best Entertainment by past attendees\\)\, exclusive wines and delicious
  culinary pairings. Raise a glass\, sing along and kick off your Passport 
 weekend with the crew that knows how to throw a proper party on Dry Creek!
   Pre-sale tickets are now available starting at $85 - secure your spot be
 fore they sail away!  L
LOCATION:Dry Creek Vineyard
URL:https://www.drycreekvineyard.com/events/page/1/
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Jazz Adventures
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260426T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260426T190000
UID:251219_fwjDvvIPUGMvDYomuPowg
DESCRIPTION:Welcome to my hometown of Healdsburg… in the heart of Sonoma
  wine country\, a town so special that Condé Nast named it one of the fin
 est cities in the country.\n\nI invite you into our world… where our fri
 endships with winemakers\, chefs\, and musicians will create an unforgetta
 ble Adventure just for you. An intimate group trip\, you’ll start each d
 ay from the boutique Hotel Healdsburg in the center of our charming town a
 nd every moment is personally curated by us. We’ll take you to the world
 -renowned regions of Russian River Valley\, Alexander Valley and Sonoma Va
 lley. Along the way\, you’ll enjoy private winery visits to the uber-lux
 ury Robert Young Winery\, the site of one of our very first dates\, and a 
 winery that Eric used to manage\, the legendary Buena Vista Winery. We’l
 l visit the most sought after cult brewery in the world\, the Russian Rive
 r Brewing Co \\(yes\, this is beer in Sonoma as well… trust us … we kn
 ow our alcohol\\).\n\nOh\, you will eat… and eat very well at my favorit
 e Sonoma restaurants including dinner at The Dry Creek Kitchen\, and a pri
 vate lunch that may include more lobster than you’ve ever seen in one pl
 ace\, and of course\, dinner at the most popular restaurant in Healdsburg\
 , The Matheson. You’ll understand why when you visit!\n\nWe love to eat 
 and drink\, but what sets our Adventures apart is the music… a truly exc
 lusive experience you won’t find anywhere else. I will host intimate pri
 vate concerts with my friends and guest musicians\, set in stunning locati
 ons across picturesque Sonoma. Some past artists have included Vincent Ing
 ala\, Richard Elliot\, Peter White and Rick Braun.\n\nAnd\, if you’re in
 terested in extending your stay with me\, there is an optional one-day  ex
 tension add-on that has become the signature day of our domestic Adventure
 s\, where you will experience the very finest Sonoma has to offer.\n\nI ca
 n’t wait to welcome you into this extraordinary place\, a little slice o
 f heaven we call home!\n\nCheers! Mindi 🎶 \\+ Eric 🍷
LOCATION:Hotel Healdsburg
URL:https://www.bandsintown.com/e/106668066?app_id=pkvts0on0m&came_from=28
 7&utm_medium=api&utm_source=partner_api&utm_campaign=event
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
