DESCRIPTION:Ancient Future leader Matthew Montfort is holding three 45-min
 ute free in-person music workshops on Wednesday\, April 29\, 2026\, at the
  Cloverdale Arts Alliance in Sonoma County. At 6:30 PM\, an introductory B
 eginning Guitar workshop helps aspiring guitarists get started on the righ
 t track with good practice habits. At 7:15 PM\, an Intermediate Guitar wor
 kshop teaches chords\, songs\, theory\, and music notation. At 8 PM\, lear
 n to play and recite rhythms at the International Rhythms workshop\, which
  can help any musician or dancer improve their rhythm skills. Ongoing musi
 c classes will then be offered on Wednesday evenings tailored to the indiv
 idual goals of participants. An inspiring music instructor who helps stude
 nts of all levels and ages learn whatever style they desire\, Montfort is 
 on the 100 Greatest Acoustic Guitarists list at DigitalDreamDoor.com along
  with luminaries like Michael Hedges and Merle Travis. To sign up for the 
 workshops\, email lessons@matthewmontfort.com.
LOCATION:Cloverdale Arts Alliance
URL:https://www.ancient-future.com/news2026.html#workshop
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
