BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Small Wonders
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260430T110000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260430T170000
UID:260324BDNscltqI0GldI1JwrF7Rw
DESCRIPTION:Call for Art: Small Wonders\n\nSome of the most exquisite beau
 ty can be captured in the smallest of images and objects: the iridescence 
 of a hummingbird in flight\, a millefiori paperweight\, Faberge eggs\, or 
 a miniature woven basket. These pieces are modest in size but powerful in 
 creativity and expression.\n\nHealdsburg Center for the Arts \\(HCA\\) inv
 ites artists to submit paintings\, original fine art prints\, collage\, mi
 xed media\, drawings\, fiber arts\, sculptures\, ceramics\, and jewelry fo
 r this exhibition.\n\nApplication Requirements:\n\n- Platform: All applica
 tions must be submitted via EntryThingy\n\n- Eligibility: Work must be ori
 ginal and completed within the past two years. Photos in the application m
 ust represent the actual work intended for exhibition.\n\n- Size/Weight: A
 rtwork must not exceed 12" x 12" unframed \\(144 sq in\\) or 196 sq in fra
 med. Maximum weight is 40 lbs.\n\n- Display: 2-D pieces must be securely w
 ired \\(no alligator clips\\). 3-D work must be stable\; artists are respo
 nsible for on-site assembly if required.\n\n- Sales: All work must be for 
 sale. HCA retains a 40% commission\; artists receive 60%. Please list reta
 il prices only.\n\nKey Dates:\n\n- Entry Deadline: May 10\, 2026 \\(9 PM\\
 )\n\n- Notification of Selection: By May 13\, 2026\n\n- Shipped Work Deadl
 ine: Wednesday\, May 27\, 2026 \\(must include pre-paid return label\\)\n\
 n- Hand-Delivery: Sunday\, May 31 \\(12–4 PM\\) and Monday\, June 1 \\(1
 1 AM–1 PM\\)\n\n- Exhibition Dates: June 4\, 2026 – July 19\, 2026\n\n
 - Opening Reception: Saturday\, June 6\, 2026 \\(4–6 PM\\)\n\n- Pick-up/
 Return Shipping: July 19 \\(12–4 PM\\) and July 20 \\(11 AM–1 PM\\)\; 
 shipping the week of July 20.\n\nEntry Fees:\n\n- Non-Members: $50 \\(1 en
 try\\)\, $55 \\(2 entries\\)\, $60 \\(3 entries\\). Includes a $60 yearly 
 supporter membership.\n\n- Current Members: $40 \\(1 entry\\)\, $45 \\(2 e
 ntries\\)\, $50 \\(3 entries\\).
LOCATION:Healdsburg Center for the Arts
URL:https://healdsburgcenterforthearts.org/small-wonders-2/
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Art Exhibit: The Poetic Landscape
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260430T110000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260430T180000
UID:260318lQ6fROtyTUG8a-t2hqA3Bg
DESCRIPTION:Date: FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE  3/13/26\n\nAPRIL EXHIBIT: THE PO
 ETIC LANDSCAPE\n\nEXHIBIT DATES:  March 30  – April 26\, 2026\n\nRECEP
 TION: SATURDAY\, APRIL 4\, 2026\, 3-5 pm: Join us to meet KAREN MILLER and
  PHYLLIS RAPP\;  celebrate the show and enjoy a poetry reading by feature
 d guest\, Linda Loveland Reid\, gallery artist and published author.  Be 
 sure to take part in the Gallery’s free monthly drawing for a beautiful 
 work by a Gallery artist.  Refreshments will be served.\n\nSonoma County 
 artist\, Karen Miller\, presents The Poetic Landscape\, pastel paintings t
 hat convey Miller’s personal experience in connecting with the intrinsic
  beauty of natural places. In these pieces\, color\, fluid shapes and rhyt
 hmic design combine to create an uplifting mood – a true poetic interlud
 e.  Evoking a happy mood\, “Geyserville Sunflowers\,” turning to the 
 sun by nature\, joyfully dance in its luminescence. By the river’s edge\
 , concentric reflections conjure a calm sense of wellbeing in “Fetch.”
   The viewer feels welcomed by a warm embrace entering a shaded secret sp
 ot in “September Trellis.”  Focused on local scenes\, these works tru
 ly hone in on the stunning landscape out our doors.  Miller remarked “ 
 As I contemplate the very real places of beauty surrounding us\, I try to 
 express my painterly response in hopes it will engender recognition by the
  viewers.” \n\nMeet the artist: Miller will be hosting the Gallery on M
 arch 30\, April 5 & 15 from 11am to 2:30 pm.\n\n The Stairway Smallworks 
 Showcase features Phyllis Rapp’s Magic Moments\, a collection of waterco
 lors that create an atmosphere that is both introspective and magical.  F
 amiliar domestic scenes are transformed as humans interact with animals an
 d birds in floral settings.  In “Silent Watcher” the red-headed young
  woman’s green eyes lock onto ours as she stares ahead\, flanked by her 
 avian companion.  Experiencing these works is a like taking a mini-step o
 n the wild side\, an exciting and fun experience.\n\nMeet the artist: Rapp
  will be hosting the Gallery on March 30 and April 10 from 11am to 6 pm.\n
 \nAlso join us for ART NITE HEALDSBURG\, Thursday\, April 2\, 5 – 6 pm.
   The theme for the 2026 kickoff event is Bouquets to Art.  ART NITE Hea
 ldsburg\, held the 1st Thursday of Every Month\, is a community event cele
 brating art and creativity with over 20 galleries participating.  ArtNite
 Healdsburg.com.\n\nUpstairs Art Gallery\, 306 Center Street\, Healdsburg\,
  CA 95448. \\(707\\) 431-4214.: OPEN DAILY: 11am – 6 pm.    www.upsta
 irsart gallery.net \n\nFor further information: Contact: Beverly Bird\, Pr
 ess Contact\, at bvdrio@sonic.net or 707-799-1490.
LOCATION:Upstairs Art Gallery
URL:http://www.upstairsartgallery.net
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Samba no Pé - First Class
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260430T183000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260430T193000
UID:260317cbDMKF6nKkSTQjfWzgO6nw
DESCRIPTION:Get ready to feel the rhythm and energy of Rio de Janeiro! Sa
 mba no Pé \\(Samba in the Foot\\) is the captivating solo style of samba
  danced in the streets and at Carnival\, known for its rapid\, intricate f
 ootwork and infectious hip movements.\n\nYou will learn\n\nThe Basic Step:
  You will master the signature quick-quick-slow rhythm that defines Samba 
 no Pé.\n\nArm & Hip Styling: You will learn how to add the authentic flai
 r\, movement\, and energy that makes Brazilian samba so captivating.\n\nTe
 chnique & Posture: You will receive tips on proper body alignment to help 
 you dance longer\, faster\, and more safely.\n\nRhythm & Musicality: You w
 ill learn how to connect your movement directly to the irresistible beat o
 f the bateria \\(the samba drum section\\).\n\nThis class is perfect for a
 nyone looking to connect with the vibrant spirit of Brazil\, improve coord
 ination\, and get a fantastic workout—all while learning the foundationa
 l steps of this iconic dance. No partner or prior dance experience is requ
 ired! Just bring your enthusiasm and comfortable shoes!\n\nDate & Time: Th
 ursdays @6:30PM – 7:30PM\n\nAddress: 4140 Redwood Highway \\#8 San Rafae
 l\, CA\n\nNote: Arrive 10 minutes before. No floor marking shoe soles allo
 wed.
LOCATION:4140 Redwood Highway #8 • San Rafael
URL:https://salsadancemarin.com/samba-no-pe
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Valley of the Moon Music Festival Concert
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260430T170000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260430T183000
UID:260315qKp9AjrVOkipp4FsgRsvjg
DESCRIPTION:Jack London Park Partners welcomes the Valley of the Moon Musi
 c Festival\, Sonoma’s premier chamber music festival\, for an intimate c
 oncert on the second floor of the House of Happy Walls.   The program wi
 ll feature works by Antonín Dvořák\, performed by Valley of the Moon Mu
 sic Festival Directors - cellist Tanya Tomkins and pianist Eric Zivian - a
 longside critically acclaimed violinist Tien-Hsin Cindy Wu.   The event 
 begins with a wine reception at 5-5:30 p.m.\n\nAll proceeds benefit Jack L
 ondon Park Partners’ Education programs.\n\nThe **Valley of the Moon Mu
 sic Festival** presents chamber music from across the centuries perform
 ed on historical instruments and was recently voted ***Best Chamber Music
  Festival*** in the ***San Francisco Classical Voice Audience Choice Awa
 rds.*** Each summer\, the VMMF brings world-renowned artists and exceptio
 nal emerging musicians to Sonoma for performances and training programs th
 at foster artistic excellence\, historical insight\, and deep community en
 gagement.\n\nThis year is VMMF’s 12th Season and events will run from
  July 9-26 in Sonoma.  For more information\, visit https://valleyofthem
 oonmusicfestival.org/. \n\nAccess to the venue is by stairs. For informat
 ion about access\, call 707-938-5216.
LOCATION:Jack London State Historic Park
URL:https://jacklondonpark.com/events/valley-of-the-moon-music-festival-co
 ncert/
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Bring Back the Build Forum
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260430T170000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260430T193000
UID:260314gzYONXMS0U22m1a-Ch1x3w
DESCRIPTION:Join the LIME Foundation for the Bring Back the Build Forum on
  April 30 from 5:00–7:30 PM at the Sonoma Clean Power Customer Center.\n
 \nThis event will bring together local contractors\, industry leaders\, an
 d workforce partners for an evening focused on the future of the trades. A
 ttendees will have the opportunity to network\, exchange ideas\, and discu
 ss emerging topics impacting the construction and skilled trades industrie
 s.\n\nTopics of discussion will include:\n\n• Workforce development and 
 building the next generation of skilled trades professionals\n\n• How AI
  and technology are impacting the industry\n\n• Using social media and d
 igital tools to grow your business\n\n• Industry trends and opportunitie
 s for collaboration\n\nGuests will also have the opportunity to tour Sonom
 a Clean Power’s facility and meet graduates from the LIME Foundation’s
  NextGen Trades Academy. These graduates are currently seeking employment 
 opportunities with local companies.\n\nWhether you're a contractor\, busin
 ess owner\, or industry professional\, this forum is a chance to connect\,
  learn\, and help strengthen the future workforce of our region.\n\nFood a
 nd drinks will be provided.\n\n**Please RSVP by April 23 at www.bringbackt
 hebuild.com**\n\nIf you have any questions\, please contact ale@thelimefo
 undation.org or call 707-532-5463.\n\nTo learn more about the LIME Founda
 tion\, visit www.thelimefoundation.org.
LOCATION:Sonoma Clean Power
URL:http://www.bringbackthebuild.com
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
