BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Postcards - Spring 2026 Concert Series
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260501T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260501T210000
UID:260405ODYJGwPMcEWELlIibQUVCw
DESCRIPTION:The Occidental Community Choir puts on live concerts featuring
  an eclectic mix of locally composed music\, classical and contemporary ch
 oral pieces\, poetry\, and spoken word from our community in the redwoods 
 of Northern California.\n\nThe Occidental Community Choir invites audience
 s to its Spring concert series\, Postcards\, a musical journey through mem
 ory\, connection\, and the moments that shape our lives.\n\nIn times that 
 can feel uncertain or isolating\, even small gestures of connection—a po
 stcard\, a call\, a simple message saying “I’m thinking of you”—ca
 n remind us that we are not alone. Postcards is built around that spirit o
 f reaching out. Each piece in the program serves as a musical postcard: a 
 snapshot from a particular time and place\, carrying stories of joy\, long
 ing\, hope\, and reflection.\n\nSome of these musical postcards arrive bri
 ght and sun-drenched\; others carry the weathered edges of memory. Togethe
 r they form a collection of moments that remind us our lives are measured 
 not only in years\, but in the experiences that stay with us and the ones 
 we share with others. Through song\, the choir becomes both sender and rec
 ipient—offering voices as messages of care\, presence\, and connection. 
 Postcards is a reminder that even in difficult times\, music can help us r
 each across distance and say something simple and powerful: you matter\, y
 ou are connected\, and you are not alone.\n\nJoin the Occidental Community
  Choir this spring for an evening of music that carries stories\, memories
 \, and hope into a weary and waiting world.
LOCATION:Occidental Center for the Arts
URL:https://www.pressdemocrat.com/events/#/details/postcards-spring-2026-c
 oncert-series/18501368/2026-05-01T19
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
