BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Monica Da Silva & Complicated Animals
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260501T170000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260501T000000
UID:260327nFRgRVv-OkqnzyoulV34dQ
DESCRIPTION:Monica da Silva grew up living between The United States and B
 elém\, Brazil\, a city on the Amazon River. A love of travel and foreign 
 language helped to forge her unique sound. \n\n \n\nParalleling her life\,
  da Silva's music contains an eclectic mix of Brazilian and American influ
 ences. Her sound can be classified as International Fusion\, as it is heav
 ily influenced by Brazilian music\, namely Bossa Nova\, but also incorpora
 tes elements of Lounge\, Electronica\, Indie Pop\, and Worldbeat. Da Silva
  brings her cultural diversity to her songs\, smoothly flowing between Eng
 lish\, Portuguese\, and Spanish.\n\n \n\nIn 2010\, da Silva released her a
 lbum "Brasilissima" . The record featured songs in both of her native lang
 uages - English and Portuguese. The first single "Aí Então"\, “was cho
 sen by Putumayo World Music to be included on their compilation “Brazili
 an Beat”. The upbeat\, psychedelic track "That's Not The Way" was chosen
  by the music director of ESPN to be played during the programming of The 
 FIFA World Cup in 2014\, alongside major recording artists Coldplay\, Sér
 gio Mendes\, Pitbull\, Jennifer Lopez\, The Black Eyed Peas\, Stan Getz\, 
 and Astrud Gilberto. \n\nDa Silva's single "Soldado de Amor" \\(2017\\) ha
 s been featured in the BBC One series "The Replacement”\, in the Paramou
 nt Network series "American Woman"\, and in a 2019 campaign for the design
 er Tory Burch.\n\nHer music has also been featured in the series "Heartlan
 d"\, and in an ad for Patron Tequila. She is currently recording a new\, f
 ull-length solo album\, as well as writing and recording with her project\
 , Complicated Animals.
LOCATION:Pax Mahle Wines
URL:https://www.bandsintown.com/e/107954593?app_id=pkvts0on0m&came_from=28
 7&utm_medium=api&utm_source=partner_api&utm_campaign=event
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Callie Watts
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260501T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260501T000000
UID:260327aex_6M7fREKf7MqDWnHAuw
DESCRIPTION:Callie Watts is a singer/songwriter from Northern California w
 ho was raised on classical music\, The Beatles and The Beach Boys before d
 iscovering Joni Mitchell\, Elton John\, Stevie Wonder\, Paul Simon\, Billy
  Joel\, Carole King\, and all the great writers of the ’60s and 70’s w
 ho have influenced her sound and writing style. After graduating high scho
 ol\, Callie began playing and performing solo\, as well as in local and ba
 y area bands of different genres. She’s played blues with Eric Lindell a
 nd the Reds\, funky soul with Phatty\, and jazz/swing with Savoy Swingers 
 along with many other various projects. Callie has taken turns throughout 
 her career as a keyboardist\, guitarist\, writer\, and lead/backing vocali
 st\, and she’s currently a member of the dynamic Sonoma County funk rock
  band Burrows and Dilbeck\, having joined in 2010 as part of the former ba
 nd Frobeck. Over time\, she’s had the honor of opening for acts such as 
 Bootsy Collins\, Elvin Bishop\, Huey Lewis and The News\, War\, Ozomatli\,
  Bill Champlin\, Booker T\, and the B52s. Callie continues to perform freq
 uently as an acoustic solo artist\, focusing on developing a core audience
  and a buzz for her original material. Come hang out and listen at venues 
 such as Aroma Roasters\, Rincon Valley Tap Room and Bottle Shop\, and Hopm
 onk Tavern.
LOCATION:HopMonk Tavern Novato
URL:https://www.bandsintown.com/e/108008901?app_id=pkvts0on0m&came_from=28
 7&utm_medium=api&utm_source=partner_api&utm_campaign=event
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
